        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 29 at 3:11PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 311 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Haddam, or near East Hampton, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Colchester and East Hampton around 315 PM EDT.
Salem and Lebanon around 330 PM EDT.
Bozrah around 340 PM EDT.
Sprague around 350 PM EDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter.

Heavy rain is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
